.SH NAME
dotty-signing-key - Create and use SSH signing keys on hardware security keys.


.SH SYNOPSIS
\fBdotty signing-key  [flags]\fP


.SH DESCRIPTION
Signing keys are resident FIDO2 credentials on a YubiKey, used to sign
git commits, tags, and files via ssh-keygen. dotty keeps only key-handle
stubs on disk (under the private $XDG_DATA_HOME/dotty/security-key) — the
secret never leaves the hardware. Keys are PIN-protected (verify-required)
and need no touch per signature.


.SH OPTIONS
\fB-h\fP, \fB--help\fP[=false]
	help for signing-key

.PP
\fB--security-key\fP=""
	security key to use: a serial number or an alias

.PP
\fB--username\fP=""
	username the key is enrolled under (default: the current user)


.SH OPTIONS INHERITED FROM PARENT COMMANDS
\fB--profile\fP=""
	profile to operate on (defaults to the active profile)


.SH EXAMPLE
.EX
  dotty signing-key new
  dotty signing-key list
  dotty signing-key get --security-key=work
  dotty signing-key sign --print-git-config
.EE


.SH SEE ALSO
\fBdotty(1)\fP, \fBdotty-signing-key-get(1)\fP, \fBdotty-signing-key-import(1)\fP, \fBdotty-signing-key-list(1)\fP, \fBdotty-signing-key-new(1)\fP, \fBdotty-signing-key-sign(1)\fP
